Introduction Thousands of times I&rsquo;ve heard of the Gene Set Enrichment Analysis or GSEA. Thousands of times I tried to run it and thousands of times I failed!
As lucky as it can get my recent collaborative work required me to run GSEA. I thought this time I will finally figure out how to do it. As usual it didn&rsquo;t work out well&hellip;
First of all, there are millions of R tools which can run GSEA analysis.

At ISMB-2015 in Dublin I presented a poster on my previous PostDoc project: &ldquo;Perturbations of PIP3 signalling trigger a global remodelling of gene expression and reveal a transcriptional feedback loop.&rdquo;
You can view/download the poster at F1000 website. All ISMB posters submitted to F1000 can be viewed at their channel.
